<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/417a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-20T17:00:00-05:00">November 20, 1929—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>305. The President deems it wiser, until after the outcome of the
                            forthcoming discussions with the members of the Japanese delegation on
                            their way to London, for you to refrain from discussing the question of
                            the Japanese ratio with Matsudaira, in order that any possible
                            misunderstanding or confusion on this delicate subject may be
                            avoided.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>